In 2010, four teachers in the Beginner/Intermediate Lounge (BIL) came together to develop a program for those aspiring to learn the game.  With the hard work and support of Maureen Hall, Founder and Manager of the BIL, they developed the four courses of the Beginning Bridge Program—64 hours of intense, interactive learning.|
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


AT|

Maureen has devoted much of her life during the past 10 years toward providing a ‘safe haven’ of learning opportunities for beginning and intermediate bridge players. Because of her endless effort, many BILies become excellent players not to mention lifelong friends.|
PG| ***** 2 ***** |


AT|

In the 2011 segment of the Beginning Bridge Program, a group of students formed a team they called the “Kings and Queens.”  Nearly three years later the original Kings and Queens and several BIL friends they made along the way are meeting in Las Vegas for the summer 2014 NABC, one flying in as far as the UK.|
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


AT|

The four founding instructors of the Beginning Bridge Program were Roberta, BBO nickname "robzim", national junior German champion Albrecht Hollstein, BBO nickname "xx1943", Howard and Sandy. |
PG| ***** 4 ***** |


AT|

Howard, who taught the team defense in the Program’s Bridge 202, offered to coach them in three rigorous sessions before they departed for f2f competition at the Vegas tables. This presentation is based on the first session held on July 3, 2014.|
PG| ***** 5 ***** |


