^B@2^*BHoward Schutzman: ^*N|cp||at|Many play "Systems On-Stolen Bid Doubles" which means a double by North would mean that North intended to bid 2@S (minor suit transfer). Since, if you play stolen bid doubles, a double by North is a minor suit transfer, there is no way for North to make a penalty double. That is one of the reasons many experts play Lebensohl after interference over 1NT. |
