^B@2^*BHoward Schutzman: ^*N|cp||at|BTW, some people are worried about their being able to make 6N. In general, playing in a suit in slam is almost always safer than playing in NT, although not on this hand as it turns out. When playing IMPs, it makes no difference whether they play in 6@H or 6N. The IMP score is exactly the same. And since we are practicing for a team game, we are worried about the best IMP bidding.|
