NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward Schutzman: ^*N|cp||at|Therefore, especially when bidding slams, you should prefer a suit slam when you have a fit to bidding 6N. It is almost always safer and easier to play. That is particularly true in IMPs, but is even true in Match Points. Having said that, it is true in both IMPs and Match Points, that it is almost always better to play 3NT than 5 of a minor.|
